ork]].\n\n===== New York City =====\nThe New York Vegetarian Vision Festival, which operated for several years during the late 1990s, was organized by NYC-based Vegetarian Vision, a nonprofit organization composed mostly of professional vegetarians from India who were largely devout [[Jain]]s or [[Hindus]].  They copied their event from the [[Boston Vegetarian Society#Boston Vegetarian Food Festival (BVFF)|Boston Vegetarian Food Festival (BVFF)]], which had copied their event from the Toronto Vegetarian Food Fair.\n\nThe current NYC Vegetarian Food Festival is organized by U.S. Veg Corp., a nonprofit founded by Sarah Gross Feoli and Nira Paliwoda.<ref>{{cite web|title=NYC Vegetarian Food Festival|url=http://nycvegfoodfest.com/|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\nLast year's two-day NYC Vegetarian Food Festival was held on May 19\u201320, 2018, at The Metropolitan Pavilion, 125 West 18th Street, in [[New York City]].  General admission is $30 each plus a $3.72 Exhibit Fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124051704/http://www.nycvegfoodfest.com/Welcome.html|title=COMING MARCH 2011|author=|date=24 November 2010|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe 11th annual Veggie Pride Parade was held on April 8, 2018, beginning in Greenwich Village/Union Square in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.veggieprideparade.org/|title=Veggie Pride Parade, New York City|website=Veggieprideparade.org|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://allevents.in/events/11th-annual-veggie-pride-parade-nyc/2265336573679443|title=11th Annual Veggie Pride Parade NYC|website=Allevents.in|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>  This is the first annual Veggie Pride Parade which was not organized by Pamela Rice and VivaVegie, which had started and organized the event for ten years.  This year's event was organized by [[The Humane League]].\n\nThe annual Vegan Street Fair New York Nights was held on Saturday, June 9, 2018, at West 8th Street between 5th & 6th, New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.veganstreetfair.com/|title=Vegan Street Fair \u2013 Vegan \u2013 Los Angeles -|author=|date=|website=Vegan Street Fair \u2013 Vegan \u2013 Los Angeles -|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  Vegan Street Fair Events is a private vegetarian-value company which profitably organizes such events in various locations around the United States.  \"VSF LA and VSF NY are our two FREE annual mainstay events.\"  \"The VSF Nights Tour has rotating cities every year while VSF LA Nights is an annual mainstay event.\"  VSF Nights are organized commercially in four American cities: [[North Hollywood]], New York, [[Seattle]], and [[Las Vegas]].  VSF began in 2015, and \"VSF and VSF Nights are expected to be in 6 US cities by 2018.\"  The additional two American cities are yet to be named.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n\n===== Buffalo =====\n\nWNY VegFest is organized by WNY Vegans. It is typically held the first Sunday in August, is free to attend, is organized by volunteers, and includes a Tofurky Trot.<ref name=\"wnyvegfest1\"/>\n\n==== North Carolina ====\n===== Asheville =====\n\nThe Asheville Vegan Fest is scheduled for June 8\u201310, 2018, in Pack Square Park at 80 Court Square Park in downtown [[Asheville, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://veganfest.bwar.org/|title=VeganFest|author=|date=|website=bwar.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  All three days of events are free to the public, and Sunday's Asheville VeganFest Outdoor Festival runs from 11am to 6pm.\n\n===== Charlotte =====\nThe 7th Annual Charlotte VegFest for 2018 is scheduled for Freedom Hall at the Park Expo and Conference Center, 800 Briar Creek Road, in [[Charlotte, North Carolina]] for Saturday, October 13, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/CharlotteVegFest/|title=Charlotte Vegfest|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://veganclt.com/charlotte-vegfest/about/|title=When is Charlotte VegFest?|author=|date=|website=veganclt.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The 6th Annual Charlotte VegFest, the region's largest vegan festival, was held in April 2017 at the Park Expo, from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m.  Speakers included Will Tucker, professional vegan bodybuilder, and The Good Food Institute's Emily Byrd.  More than 100 exhibitors were featured, as were VegSpeedDating and vegan culinary demonstrations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://clture.org/charlotte-veg-fest/|title=Why you should check out Charlotte VegFest|author=|date=27 April 2017|website=clture.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Wilmington =====\nWilmington Vegan's First Wilmington Vegfest was held on Saturday, April 14, 2018, at the Coastline Conference Center, 501 Nutt Street, in [[Wilmington, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wilmingtonvegan.com/wilmington-vegfest/|title=Wilmington VegFest|website=Wilmington Vegan}}</ref><ref name=\"facebook.com\">{{cite web|url=https://facebook.com/ncvegfests|title=Wilmington Vegfest|website=Facebook.com}}</ref>  Reportedly, this nonprofit event is being organized by the Executive Director from Triangle VegFest, which is sponsored annually by Triangle Vegetarian Society.\n\n==== Ohio ====\n===== Cleveland =====\nThe 2018 Cleveland VegFest was held for May 5, 2018, from 11:00 AM \u2013 7:00 PM, at the [[Huntington Convention Center of Cleveland]] at 300 Lakeside Ave East.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clevelandvegansociety.org/|title=Welcome|website=The Cleveland Vegan Society}}</ref>  Admission was free, but a $5 donation was requested at the door.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clevelandvegansociety.org/vegfest-home|title=VegFest Home|author=|date=|website=The Cleveland Vegan Society|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The 2019 Cleveland VegFest is scheduled for May 18, 2019, again from 11:00 AM \u2013 7:00 PM, at the [[Huntington Convention Center of Cleveland]], and with the same free admission but $5 donation requested.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://raisevegan.com/prep-up-cleveland-veg-fest-2019-coming-up-on-may-18th/|title=Prep Up! Cleveland Veg Fest 2019 Coming Up on May 18th|date=11 May 2019|website=Raise Vegan|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Columbus =====\nThe first ever Columbus VegFest was held on September 17, 2017, and is expected to be held each August or September.  The date of the second Columbus VegFest has not yet been determined.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140517062013/http://columbusvegfest.com/]</ref><ref name=\"facebook.com\"/>\n\n==== Oklahoma ====\n===== Oklahoma City =====\nThe Buddha Mind Veggie Fest is organized by Buddha Mind Monastery of [[Fo Guang Shan]], and scheduled for June 2018 at 5800 South Anderson Road in [[Oklahoma City]].  The event is free of charge and open to the public, and all food will be vegan-compliant.<ref>http://www.ctbuddhamind.org/veggierevised.pdf</ref>\n\n==== Oregon ====\n===== Portland =====\nThe VegOut! Events Portland Vegan Beer & Food Festival, organized by VegOut! Events is scheduled for July 21\u201322, 2018, to be held at Holladay Park in [[Portland, OR]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegoutevents.com/|title=VegOut! Events|website=VegOut! Events}}</ref>\n\n==== Pennsylvania ====\n===== Bethlehem =====\nThe annual Bethlehem Vegfest was held in southside Bethlehem in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bethlehem Vegfest|url=http://www.downtownbethlehemassociation.com/events/vegfest|website=Downtownbethlehemassociation.com|accessdate=19 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150907205637/http://www.downtownbethlehemassociation.com/events/vegfest|archive-date=7 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The 4th annual Bethlehem VegFest is again scheduled for July 14, 2018, in the SouthSide Bethlehem Greenway, 316 S New Street, [[Bethlehem, Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://10times.com/vegfest-bethlehem|title=Bethlehem VegFest|author=|date=|website=10times.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  \"This event features cooking demonstrations, renowned speakers, live music, as well as over 100 food, small business, and craft vendors from up and down the east coast.\"\n\n===== Erie =====\nThe Erie VegFest of the Erie Vegan and Vegetarian Society happens in the fall in [[Erie, Pennsylvania|Erie]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ErieVegFest|url=http://www.ErieVegFest.org/|website=Ericvegfest.org|accessdate=30 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n===== Johnstown =====\nThe annual NAVS Vegan Summerfest was held at the [[University of Pittsburgh-Johnstown]] from July 4\u20138, 2018, in [[Johnstown, Pennsylvania]].  About 600 registered for the 5-day annual event.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://summerfest.navs-online.org/|title=Vegan Summerfest \u2013 Sign Up For Our 45th Annual Conference|author=|date=|website=Summerfest|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://summerfest.navs-online.org/|title=Vegan Summerfest &#124; Learn The Health Benefits of a Vegan Lifestyle|website=Summerfest|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>  The event will be held at UP until further notice.  Vegan cookbook author and culinary celebrity Chef AJ was admitted to The Vegan Hall of Fame, previously The Vegetarian Hall of Fame, and given the annual award.\n\n===== Lancaster =====\nThe annual 2018 Lancaster VegFest was held on June 2, 2018, from 12 noon to 5 pm, in Buchanan Park in [[Lancaster, Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pavegfest.com/|title=Lancaster PA VegFest \u2013 A Plant Based and Vegan Festival in Lancaster City|author=|date=|website=Lancaster Vegfest|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Philadelphia =====\nAfter a 2-year hiatus, the annual Philly VegFest, or Philadelphia VegFest, was held on Saturday, June 9, 2018, at Bainbridge Green, 300 Bainbridge Street, in [[Philadelphia]].  No Philly VegFest had been held in 2016 or 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eventbrite.com/e/46248782353?aff=efbneb|title=Philly VegFest|author=|date=|website=Eventbrite|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.meetup.com/Main-Line-Vegan-Meetup/events/248631069/|title=PHILLY VEG FEST 2018!!!|author=|date=|website=Meetup|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phillymag.com/be-well-philly/2018/04/12/philadelphia-vegan-food-vegfest/|title=Philly's Huge Vegan Food Festival Is Returning in June After a Two-Year Hiatus|author=|date=12 April 2018|website=phillymag.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phillymag.com/be-well-philly/2018/05/24/philadelphia-vegfest-vegan-festival/|title=Take a Look at the Vendors Lined Up for Philly's Huge Vegan Food Festival|author=|date=24 May 2018|website=phillymag.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/PhiladelphiaVegFest/|title=Philadelphia Vegfest|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.paeats.com/|title=PA Eats \u2014 Pennsylvania food + drink videos, recipes and stories|author=|date=|website=PA Eats|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Pittsburgh =====\nThe free annual Pittsburgh VegFest is held every summer in the North Side.<ref>{{cite web|title=PittsburghVegFest|url=http://www.pittsburghvegfest.org/|website=Pittsburghvegfest.org|accessdate=30 June 2016}}</ref>  The inaugural '''Pittsburgh VegFest''' took place in 2015 with an attendance of over 4,000 people from all over the metro area and visitors from Virginia, West Virginia, Erie, Buffalo, Philadelphia and New Jersey.\n\nThe '''Pittsburgh Vegan Festival''' \u2013 Spring Edition \u2013 which was begun in 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/pittsburgh-vegan-festival-spring-edition-2015/1545237529071428/|title=Pittsburgh Vegan Festival \u2013 Spring Edition 2015|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> is scheduled for its fourth year sometime in mid-May at the Unitarian Universal Church of North Hills, 2359 West Ingomar Road, in [[Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania]], and runs from 12 noon to 8 pm.  All children and others under age 16 must be accompanied by an adult in order to be admitted free, and $5 cash admission is charged for all others, at the door.  No pre-event ticket sales is handled.  It is considered to be Pittsburgh's largest vegan event.\n\nThe 11th Pittsburgh Vegan Festival was held on Saturday, October 28, 2017 12\u20136 p.m, and featured Dr. [[Neal Barnard]] of [[Physicians Committee for Responsible Medicine]], among other speakers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/Food/the-11th-pittsburgh-vegan-festival-w-dr-neal-barnard-of-pcrm/1890816304575312/|title=The 11th Pittsburgh Vegan Festival w/ Dr. Neal Barnard of PCRM|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Portland =====\nA vegan beer and food festival is held in Portland in the summer.  The 2019 festival called itself the \"2nd annual.\" <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegoutevents.com/portland2019|title=VegOut! Portland Vegan Beer & Food Festival|website=VegOut!Events Portland 2019}}</ref>\n\nVegFest is a two-day event held in mid-November at the [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]] convention center, with the attendance of many vegan vendors and companies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegfest|url=https://nwveg.org/vegfest|accessdate=13 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== Puerto Rico ====\n===== Fajardo =====\nThe annual bilingual Puerto Rico Vegan Fest was held on February 25, 2018, in the Puerto Rico Convention Center in Fajardo, Puerto Rico.  The annual bilingual Puerto Rico Vegan Fest promotes plant-based diets and vegan values as effective, viable, and sustainable working solutions for human health problems and for ethical and ecological crises.  Attendance is free, as was participation for qualifying tablers promoting plant-based vegan diets and values.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.puertoricoveganfest.com/|title=Pr\u00f3ximo Evento/Next Event|website=Puerto Rico Vegan Fest}}</ref>  The bilingual vegan event was funded by a GoFundMe page.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gofundme.com/puerto-rico-vegan-fest-2018|title=Click here to support Puerto Rico Vegan Fest 2018 organized by Valerie Soto|author=|date=|website=gofundme.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== El Faro (lighthouse) Rincon =====\nThe Puerto Rico Vegan Fest was held in El Faro (lighthouse) Rincon, on Saturday, April 14, 2018.  Attendance and qualifying tabler participation promoting vegan values, food, and practices was free for everyone.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/VegFestPuertoRico/|title=VegFest Puerto Rico|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/380626832364849|title=Puerto Rico VegFest|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Patillas =====\nVive Sano, Vive Mejor Vegan Fest, the Patillas VeganFest, is scheduled for June 4, 2018, from 11 am to 7 pm.  Waleska Rodriguez<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/category/Community/Waleska-Rodr\u00edguez-Lifestyle-375740999109447/|title=Waleska Rodr\u00edguez Lifestyle|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> of mega TV Conectao's por la cocina will be featured, along with many other tablers, speakers, and presenters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/patillasveganfest/|title=Vive Sano, Vive Mejor Vegan Fest|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== South Carolina ====\n===== Mount Pleasant =====\nThe Charleston Sol-Food Veg Fest was held on Saturday, April 28, 2018, from 10 am to 6 pm, at The Grove at [[Patriots Point]] in [[Mount Pleasant, South Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csfvegfest.com/|title=Charleston Sol Veg Fest|last=Kraftives|website=csfvegfest.com}}</ref>  The rain date is May 5, 2018.  It is funded by a GoFundMe page.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gofundme.com/charleston-sol-food-veg-fest|title=Click here to support Charleston Sol Food Veg Fest organized by Charleston Sol Food Veg Fest|website=gofundme.com}}</ref>\n\n==== Tennessee ====\n===== Nashville =====\nThe Third Annual Nashville VegFest was held for April 7, 2018, at the [[Nashville Fairgrounds]] in [[Nashville, Tennessee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nashvillevegfest.com/|title=Nashville VegFest \u2013 Welcome to Nashville VegFest|website=Nashvillevegfest.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>  Tickets are sold, so the event is open to the general public but doesn't offer free admission.\n\n==== Texas ====\n\n===== Austin =====\nThe annual Texas VegFest is held in Austin.<ref>{{cite web|title=Texas VegFest in Austin|url=http://www.texasvegfest.com/|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>  The 2018 Texas VegFest was held April 7, 2018, in Fiesta Gardens at 2101 Jesse E. Segovia Street, [[Austin, Texas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.texasvegfest.com/|title=Texas VegFest|website=Texasvegfest.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref> The 2020 VEGANCHILL Fest \u2013 ATX 2020 is scheduled for February 23, 2020, and the Texas VegFest 2020 is scheduled for Apr 4, 2020, each in [[Austin, Texas|Austin]].\n\n===== Dallas =====\nTexas Veggie Fair is the longest running vegfest in Texas, established 2010 in Dallas. The ninth annual Texas Veggie Fair will be held on Saturday, Oct. 27, 2018, at Reverchon Park in Dallas.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.texasveggiefair.com/|title=Texas Veggie Fair VegFest in Dallas|author=|date=|website=Texas Veggie Fair VegFest in Dallas|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Houston =====\nVegFest Houston is hosted annually by the Vegan Society of P.E.A.C.E. and was first held in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2011|title=VegFest Houston 2011 \u2013 The Premier Vegan Festival of Texas! Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=www.vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  This vegan community festival is dedicated to \"Promoting an ethical, compassionate and sustainable world for all\".<ref>{{cite web|title=VegFest Houston|url=http://www.vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston|website=Vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>  \"VegFest Houston was held at Pecore Hall in 2011 and 2012,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2012|title=VegFest Houston 2012 \u2013 The Premier Vegan Festival of Texas! Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=www.vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and then moved to the larger Pershing Middle School campus for 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2013.php|title=VegFest Houston 2013 \u2013 The Premier Vegan Community Festival of Texas! Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2014|title=VegFest Houston 2014 Vegan Community Festival Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> The festival went on hiatus from 2015\u20132016.  The 6th annual 2018 VegFest Houston was held on July 21, 2018, from 10 am to 5 pm, in Stafford Centre Hall in [[Houston, Texas]], where the 2017 event<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2017.php|title=VegFest Houston 2017 Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> was staged.<ref>{{cite web|title=VegFest Houston|url=http://www.vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston|website=Vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=25 January 2018}}</ref>  The event has been open to the general public and free since its first iteration, but the VIP Pass offers some attractive perks.  The organizers point out that \"Houston is ranked the 4th \"Most Veg-friendly City\" in the nation as of 2012, making us the top Texas Veg-friendly city!\"\n\nThe Vegan Rodeo Weekend \u2013 Houston is scheduled for March 28\u201329, 2020, in Houston.\n\n===== Killeen =====\n[[Killeen, Texas]] is the site of the annual American VegFests<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegevents.com/festivals/|title=Upcoming Plant-Based and Vegan Festivals|author=|date=|website=Veg Events|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> each second Saturday in January.\n\n===== Marshall =====\nHealthFest is an annual free three-day whole foods, plant-based festival that takes place every spring in historic [[Marshall, Texas]], which has been organized annually since 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=HealthFest|url=http://healthfest.com|website=Healthfest.com|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>  The 2017 Health Fest was held from March 31 through April 2, 2017 in the Marshall Civic Center, 2501 East End Blvd, in South Marshall, Texas, with 25 scheduled speakers, and was livestreamed.<ref>{{cite web|title=HealthFest|url=http://healthfest.com/|website=Healthfest.com|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref>  The 2018 3-day event was organized by Fort Worth Vegetarian Society and held at the same site on Saturday, March 31, 2018.\n\n==== Virginia ====\n===== Hampton Roads =====\nHampton Roads VegFest is held every fall in southeastern Virginia, bringing in over 2,000 people from the coastal region.<ref>{{cite web|title=HamptonRoadsVegFest|url=http://www.hamptonroadsvegfest.com/|website=Hamptonroadsvegfest.com|accessdate=8 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n===== Richmond =====\nThe Richmond VegFest is scheduled for June 2018 in Azalea Gardens at Bryan Park in [[Richmond, Virginia]]. About forty vegan food vendors participate, and general admission is free, but attendees buy food from the vendors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://veggiefest.org/|title=Richmond Veg Fest|author=|date=|website=veggiefest.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  Vegan Action and the longstanding Vegetarian Society of Richmond are primary organizers, and major cosponsors include VegFund, FOX Richmond TV, YELP Richmond, several publications, Virginia Family Dentistry with 14-locations practice with 57 general dentists and dental specialists, and a local Indian restaurant.\n\n==== Washington ====\n===== Seattle =====\nThe Seattle VegFest was held on April 7\u20138, 2018, in [[Seattle, Washington]], at the Exhibition Hall at Seattle Center which had been built for the 1962 [[Seattle World's Fair]] just north of [[Belltown, Seattle|Belltown]] in the [[Lower Queen Anne, Seattle|Uptown]] neighborhood.  Admission tickets are sold to the general public, but children under 12 are admitted free.  The sponsor, Vegetarians of Washington, organizes over 1000 volunteers for this annual event.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vegofwa.org/vegfest/|title=Vegfest|date=2 November 2015|website=Vegofwa.org|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Spokane =====\nThe Spokane Vegfest is scheduled for July 28, 2018, from 10am-6pm, at [[Spokane Community College]] in [[Spokane, Washington]].  The annual free event is organized by Inland Northwest Vegans.  Over 3000 attendees participated in the 2017 event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.inveg.org/vegfest/|title=Spokane Vegfest 2019 on July 27 @ Spokane Community College|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Wisconsin ====\n===== Glendale =====\nThe first inaugural Midwest Vegan Fest was held on Saturday, April 14, 2018, at Nicolet High School in [[Glendale, Wisconsin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://midwestveganfest.com/|title=April 14th, 2018 Nicolet High School 11am \u2013 5pm :Midwest Vegan Fest|website=Midwestveganfest.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Madison =====\nMad City Vegan Fest is organized by Alliance for Animals and held in the summer every year in [[Madison, Wisconsin]], and runs from 10 am to 5 pm.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mad City Vegan Fest|url=http://www.veganfest.org/|website=Veganfest.org|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref>  The 2017 event was held June 17, 2017, at the [[Alliant Energy Center]], and the 2018 event is envisioned for June 2018 in the same locale.<ref>https://www.veganfest.org/</ref>\n\n===== Milwaukee =====\nThe Milwaukee Veg Expo was held on Saturday, May 5, 2018, from 11:30 am \u2013 5:30pm, in the Hart Park Muellner Building in [[Milwaukee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mkevegexpo.com/|title=Milwaukee Veg Expo|website=Mkevegexpo.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Oceania ==\n\n=== Australia ===\n{{see also|Vegfest (AU)}}\n\n====Adelaide====\nThe inaugural Vegan Festival Adelaide was in 2007 and the annual event has grown in size ever since, from 1000 attendees in 2007 to 17,000 in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url =https://veganfestival.info/about|website =Vegan festival|title=About|access-date =24 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Sydney ====\n\nThe [[International Vegetarian Union]] encourages regional and national vegetarian organizations to run vegetarian festivals. The [[Vegfest (AU)|43rd World Vegfest]] was held in [[Sydney]] and [[Melbourne]] in October 2015.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|title=43rd World IVU VegFest in Australia|url=http://www.ivu.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=367:ivu-world-vegfest-in-australia&catid=21&Itemid=293|website=IVU.org|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== Melbourne ====\n\nThe [[International Vegetarian Union|IVU]] encourages regional and national organizations to run vegetarian festivals. The 43rd World Vegfest was held in Sydney and Melbourne.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/>\n\nOn November 1, Melbourne celebrates [[World Vegan Day]].<ref>{{cite web|title=World Vegan Day Melbourne|url=http://www.wvd.org.au/|website=Wvd.org.au|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== Hobart ====\n[[Hobart]]'s first vegan festival, VeganFest Tasmania, took place on November 4, 2018. It had been organized as an annual festival celebrating veganism.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://veganfesttas.com.au/ |website=VeganFest Tasmania |accessdate=27 September 2018}}</ref>  The second VeganFest Tasmania is expected to be held on Sunday, 3 November 2019, from 10 am to 4 pm, in the Kingborough Community Hub. Currently at least 48 exhibitors have been scheduled for this free event, which is open to the public.<ref>[http://veganfesttas.com.au/ VeganFest Tasmania]</ref>\n\n== South America ==\n\n===Brazil===\nVegfest Brasil happens since 2004 biennially in a different city each edition. The main organizer is the Brazilian Vegetarian Society (SVB).<br>\nStarting in 2018, Vegfest Brasil will be held annually.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vista-se.com.br/vegfest-aprendizado-polemica-e-tudo-o-que-rolou-no-maior-evento-vegetariano-da-america-latina/|title=Vegfest: aprendizado, pol\u00eamica e tudo o que rolou no maior evento vegetariano da Am\u00e9rica Latina|website=Vista-se.com.br|accessdate=4 September 2017|language=pt}}</ref><br>\n2013: [[Curitiba]]<br>\n2015: [[Recife]]<br>\n2017: [[Campos do Jord\u00e3o]]\n\n===Peru===\n\n==== Arequipa ====\nVegan Fest Arequipa 2018: May 25, 26, 27<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegan Fest Arequipa 2018|url=https://www.facebook.com/veganfestarequipa/|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== Cusco ====\nVegFest Cusco 2017: August 25, 26, 27<ref>{{cite web|title=VegFest Cusco 2017|url=https://www.facebook.com/VegFestPeru/|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[American Vegan Society]]- publishes online list of vegan-oriented VegFests in USA and Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.americanvegan.org/vegfests.htm|title=VegFests in the USA|author=|date=|website=americanvegan.org|accessdate=22 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180717212909/http://www.americanvegan.org/vegfests.htm|archive-date=17 July 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Awareness day]]\n* [[List of food days]]\n* [[List of food months]]\n* [[List of food weeks]]\n* [[List of vegetarian and vegan companies]]\n* [[List of vegetarian organizations]]\n* [[Meat-free days]]\n* [[Vegetarian week]]\n* [[Vegetarianism by country]]\n* [[World Vegan Day]]\n* [[World Vegetarian Day]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Veganism and vegetarianism|state=expanded}}\n\n[[Category:Vegetarianism]]\n[[Category:Veganism]]\n[[Category:Vegetarian festivals|and]]\n[[Category:Lists of food and drink festivals| Vege]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{Update|[[American Vegan Society]], which reported on 1/20/2018 that \"Over 120 VegFests in the United States are planned for 2018\", and this article only lists a few of them<ref>{{cite web|url=http://americanvegan.org/vegfests.htm|title=Vegfests|website=Americanvegan.org|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180122071820/http://americanvegan.org/vegfests.htm|archive-date=22 January 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>|date=February 2019}}  \n{{advert|date=March 2018}}\n{{Unreliable sources|date=January 2018}}\n{{Update|The article requires a COUNT of the number of such vegetarian festivals in each continent, and in the USA, for which the largest list of events seems to be presented.|date=October 2019}}\n}}\n\nThis is a global '''list of vegetarian and vegan festivals''', held in numerous locations around the planet, to promote veganism and/or vegetarianism among the public and to support and link individuals and organizations that practice, promote or endorse veganism or vegetarianism. Many of these events are also [[food festivals]] and/or [[music festivals]] and can also contain [[Educational entertainment|edutainment]]. Many events scheduled for Spring 2020 have been canceled because of the [[Coronovirus pandemic|coronovirus pandemic]].<ref>[https://www.happycow.net/events Happy Cow Vegan Festival Calendar, accessed 4/2/2020]</ref>\n\n== Africa ==\n=== Ghana ===\nVegfest 2015 was organized by the Vegetarian Association of Ghana.<ref name=\"wnyvegfest1\">{{cite web|title = WNY VegFest|url = http://www.wnyvegfest.com//|accessdate = 26 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Asia ==\n=== Hong Kong ===\nHong Kong Vegfest started in 2013 organized by the Hong Kong Vegan Association. The festival organisers stipulate only vegan products be offered at the event by vendors. Admission is free to attendees.\n\n=== Indonesia ===\nThe first Bali Vegan Festival started in 2015 at Down To Earth (Ubud).<ref>{{cite web|title=Bali Vegan Festival|url=http://www.baliveganfestival.com/|accessdate=26 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Japan ===\nThe Vegetarian Festival in Tokyo started in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tokyo Vegefood Fiesta|url=http://tokyo-vegefest.com/english/|website=Tokyo-vegefest.com|accessdate=21 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151015041509/http://tokyo-vegefest.com/english/|archive-date=15 October 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Philippines ===\nThe Philippines had its first 3-leg vegan festival \u2013 VegFest Pilipinas \u2013 in November and December 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=VegFest Pilipinas|url=http://vegfestpilipinas.com/|website=Vegfestpilipinas.com|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe 2017 event was two 2-day VegFest Pilipinas events at two different locations: from 18\u201319 November 2017 in Eastwood City, with 'Hair,' Pilita in concert, and VegFest Pilipinas in Chinatown the following weekend, 25\u201326 November 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegfestpilipinas.strikingly.com/|title=VegFest Pilipinas on Strikingly|author=|date=|website=VegFest Pilipinas|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astigvegan.com/vegfest-pilipinas-2017/|title=Enriquez RG. VegFest Pilipinas 2017, A Recap of what happened. December 8, 2017|author=|date=|website=astigvegan.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The 2018 event again will be two 2-day VegFest Pilipinas events at two different locations: held one weekend from 8 am to 10 pm, 18\u201319 November 2018, at the BGC Arts Center in the Eastwood Central Plaza Shopping Mall, [[Quezon City]], [[Metro Manila]], [[Philippines]]; then again, the following weekend, 25\u201326 November 2017, in Lucky Chinatown, Binondo, [[Metro Manila]], [[Philippines]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/category/Community/VegFestPilipinas/posts/|title=VegFest Pilipinas|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Singapore ===\n{{see also|EarthFest (SG)}}\nThe [[EarthFest (SG)|EarthFest Singapore]] had its debut in September 2015 and was sponsored by Singapore's [[Vegetarian Society (Singapore)|Vegetarian Society]] and others.\n\n=== Thailand ===\nThe Vegetarian Festival in Bangkok takes place each fall.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Vegetarian Festival|url=http://www.bangkok.com/whats-on-events/vegetarian-festival.htm|website=Bangkok.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{see also|Nine Emperor Gods Festival#Celebration in Thailand}}\nThis vegetarian festival is a nine-day period in October that celebrates the abstinence from meat during the ninth lunar month of the Chinese calendar.\n\n=== Vietnam ===\nThe Vegan Festival in Ho Chi Minh City takes place under the name Plant Power Celebration. The first one was held on 30 October 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/saigonveganfestival/|title=Saigon Vegan Festival|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Europe ==\n{{see also|Veganmania|VeggieWorld}}\n\n=== Belgium ===\nVegan Summer Fest is organized by BE Vegan.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegan Summer Fest|url=http://bevegan.be/vegan-summer-fest/|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Czechia ===\n[[Fluff Fest]] is an independent [[hardcore punk]] festival held each July in [[Rokycany]]. It is fully vegan, with catering provided by local animal rights organization Svoboda zv\u00ed\u0159at.<ref name=\"idioteq2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idioteq.com/a-look-inside-fluff-fest-exclusive-interview/|title=A Look Inside Fluff Fest!|first=Karol|last=Kami\u0144ski|publisher=Idioteq|date=28 January 2013|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Greece ===\nThe Vegan Life Festival (veganlife.gr) is a celebration in several Greek cities that presents vegan lifestyles, products, and practices through speeches, workshops, brochures, stalls with companies that provide vegan products, activities for children, and vegan food and sweets.  Admission open to the general public is free.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athensculturenet.com/en/event/vegan-life-festival-athens-2018|title=The Vegan Life Festival. Athens Culture Net. Accessed 12/26/2018|author=|date=|website=athensculturenet.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.veganlife.gr/|title=Veganlife|author=|date=|website=Veganlife|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  YouTube video documentation is available.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCWEP-c1VWkxt5Hcd6WQFSJw|title=Vegan Life Festival|author=|date=|website=YouTube|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Athens ====\nThe Vegan Life Festival has been held in several cities in Greece since November 5, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/%CF%84%CE%B5%CF%87%CE%BD%CF%8C%CF%80%CE%BF%CE%BB%CE%B9%CF%82-%CE%B4%CE%AE%CE%BC%CE%BF%CF%85-%CE%B1%CE%B8%CE%B7%CE%BD%CE%B1%CE%AF%CF%89%CE%BD/vegan-life-festival-2016/178401362613208/|title=Vegan Life Festival 2016|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> The 2017 Vegan Life Festival was held in Athens on July 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.veganeventhub.com/event/vegan-life-festival-athens-2017/|title=Vegan Life Festival Athens 2017|author=|date=6 June 2017|website=veganeventhub.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> Buildout plans for nine Greek cities are being implemented gradually.  Organizers claim an attendance of greater than 18,000 visitors{{citation needed|date=December 2018}} at the 2018 Athens event, held at the Technopolis of the Municipality.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaboutfestivals.gr/en/festivals/vegan-life-festival-2/|title=Vegan Life Festival 2018|author=|date=|website=allaboutfestivals.gr|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/veganlifefestival/vegan-life-festival-athens-2018/2058390741104185/|title=Vegan Life Festival Athens 2018|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/veganlifefestival/events|title=Vegan Life Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegevents.com/events/vegan-life-festival/|title=Vegan Life Festival|author=|date=|website=Veg Events|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>[https://www.happycow.net/reviews/vegan-life-festival-athens-142276 Vegan Life Festival/  HappyCow.net.  Accessed 12/26/2018]</ref>\n\n==== Thessaloniki ====\nVegan Life Festival since 2017.  The 2018 was held May 20. 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://livingcrueltyfree.gr/en/vegan-life-festival-thessaloniki-2018/|title=VEGAN LIFE FESTIVAL THESSALONIKI 2018!|last=Zoe|date=11 May 2018|website=livingcrueltyfree.gr|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Chania ====\nThe Vegan Life Festival is scheduled to begin in Chania in 2019.\n\n==== Malta ====\nFrom August 5\u20136, 2018, the Vegan Life Festival was held at The Floriana Granaries in Malta.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://veganguidegreece.com/vegan-life-festival/|title=Vegan Life Festival \u2013 Vegan Guide Greece|author=|date=|website=veganguidegreece.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Ireland ===\nDublin Vegfest is the Irish capital's vegan festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dublinvegfest.com/|title=22nd & 23rd September 2018 \u2013 Dublin Vegfest|website=dublinvegfest.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Italy ===\nVeganFest Bologna is a vegan event in Europe which had more than 43,000 visitors in 2014. The event took place in [[Bologna]] in September 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=VeganFest Bologna|url=http://www.veganfest.it/?page_id=5188|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\nFestival The Vegetarian Chance (www.thevegetarianchance.org) was founded in 2014 by journalist Gabriel Eschenazi and chef Pietro Leemann. First Festival in the world which includes a haute cuisine vegan contest with international chefs. Out of the contest the program includes show cookings, lectures, movies and a small market. Five editions were held in Milan and the last one in Turin (11-13 October). Next edition will be held on 24-25-26 October in Milan.\n\n=== Hungary ===\n\n==== Budapest ====\nThe XIX Vegetarian Festival was organized in August 2015 in [[Budapest]]. {{citation needed|date=October 2015}}\n\n=== Netherlands ===\n[[File:Psyfi.jpg|thumb|[[Psy-Fi]] in Leeuwarden, Netherlands]]\n* [[VeggieWorld]] in [[Utrecht]], since 2016, vegan<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://nos.nl/op3/artikel/2090859-gaat-het-nieuwe-vlees-het-oude-vlees-verslaan.html |title=Gaat het nieuwe vlees het oude vlees verslaan? |work=NOS |date=5 March 2016 |accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Nederlandse Vereniging voor Veganisme|VegFest]] in Utrecht, since 2014, vegan<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.trouw.nl/home/naakte-demonstranten-op-de-bres-voor-veganisme~afe5eb72/ |title=Naakte demonstranten op de bres voor veganisme |author=Amber Dujardin |work=Trouw |date=1 November 2014 |accessdate=25 March 2017}}</ref>\n* Veggie Fair in [[Lisserbroek]], since 2013, vegetarian<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.veganisme.org/event/veggiefair/ |title=VeggieFair 2016 |publisher=Nederlandse Vereniging voor Veganisme |accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe following music festivals have made a conscious decision not to sell any meat on the festival terrain: Digital Festival (DGTL) in [[Amsterdam]] (since 2016),<ref name=\"verbaasd\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.rtlnieuws.nl/nieuws/nederland/artikel/4208246/festival-milkshake-verbaasd-over-heftige-reacties-op-vegetarisch |title=Festival Milkshake verbaasd over heftige reacties op vegetarisch eten |work=RTL Nieuws |date=27 May 2018 |accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"UITgezocht\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nu.nl/uit/5291708/uitgezocht-worden-festivals-vleesvrij.html |title=UITgezocht: Worden festivals vleesvrij? |work=NU.nl |date=31 May 2018 |accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref> Lente Kabinet in [[Oostzaan]] (since 2018),<ref name=\"UITgezocht\"/> Festival Milkshake in Amsterdam (since 2018),<ref name=\"verbaasd\"/><ref name=\"UITgezocht\"/> and [[Psy-Fi]] in [[Leeuwarden]] (starting from 2019).<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.lc.nl/friesland/article24264539.ece |title=Psy-Fi verduurzaamt verder: volgende editie volledig vegetarisch |author=Yme Gietema |work=Leeuwarder Courant |date=13 March 2019 |accessdate=28 March 2019 |language=nl}}</ref> Organisers indicated their motives were sustainability and environmental protection; aside from dropping meat sales, they also focused on reducing the use of [[disposable product]]s and electricity.<ref name=\"verbaasd\"/><ref name=\"UITgezocht\"/>\n\n=== Spain ===\n\n==== Alicante ====\nVegan Fest [[Alicante]] has been organized by Alacant Rock since 2014. It is the only vegan festival in [[Spain]]. {{citation needed|date=October 2015}}\n\n=== Portugal ===\n\n==== Lisbon ====\nVegan\u00e1rio Fest [[Lisbon]] (www.veganario.org) has been organized since 2008 by a group of friends in punk/hardcore community with help of local HareKrishna Community. It is the oldest of its kind in Lisbon and has been growing in the last years. \nIt gathers a lot of organizations and small businesses and important people in the vegan community to talk about and spread veganism.\n\nThe music slowed down, it is more open to all the people. It is growing: Approximately 300/600px until 2014, more than 1500 in 2015, over 2000 in 2016, and more than 3500 in 2017.\n\n=== United Kingdom ===\n==== ''England'' ==== \n===== Birmingham =====\nBirmingham Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\">[https://www.viva.org.uk/festivals/contact#contact Contact form for VIVA's Vegan Festivals, which supplement previously existing vegan festivals in UK]</ref>\n\n===== Bournemouth =====\nApproximately 90 stalls, talks, and food.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170511025420/http://www.dorsetveganevents.co.uk/bournemouthveganfair.html|title=Bournemouth Vegan Fair \u2013 17 & 18 June 2017 \u2013 Dorset Vegan Events|author=|date=11 May 2017|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Bradford =====\nBradford Vegan Festival was held on Sunday 2 September 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/category/Community/veganfestivaluk/posts/|title=Bradford Vegan Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and again will be held in September 2019.\n\n===== Brighton =====\nBrighton Vegan Festival took place on Saturday 14 July 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/brightonveganfestival2018/|title=Brighton Vegan & Ethical Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and again will occur in July 2019.\n\nBrighton Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Bristol, Brighton, London =====\n{{see also|Vegfest (UK)}}\nVegfestUK Bristol was held May 26\u201327 at Ashton Gate stadium, Ashton Road, BS3 2EJ Bristol, United Kingdom.  Standard advance day tickets are \u00a311.00 (adults), \u00a36.00 (concessions) [including booking fees] and \u00a35.50 (children)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/ashton-gate-stadium/vegfestuk-bristol-2018/713055975565881/|title=VegfestUK Bristol 2018|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://accounts.google.com/ServiceLogin?passive=1209600&osid=1&continue=https://plus.google.com/communities/111382870961138557305&followup=https://plus.google.com/communities/111382870961138557305|title=Sign in \u2013 Google Accounts|website=accounts.google.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> but was actually held from October 27\u201328, 2018, at Olympia London. The announcement was made in September 2018, citing higher than expected costs and broad availability of good quality vegan food in Bristol, that VegFestUK organizers would not schedule another event in Bristol for 2019 or 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/ashton-gate-stadium/vegfestuk-bristol-2018/713055975565881/|title=VegfestUK Bristol 2018|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/vegfestexpress/2018/09/statement-on-the-future-of-vegfestuk-bristol|title=Statement on the future of VegfestUK Bristol|website=Statement on the future of VegfestUK Bristol|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> but that VegFestUK would continue to hold annual events elsewhere.\n\n===== Coventry =====\nCoventry Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Liverpool =====\nLiverpool Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== London =====\nJustVShow is held in July<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.justvshow.co.uk|title=Just V Show \u2013 Vegan & Vegetarian Show in London & Glasgow|website=Just V Show}}</ref> and [[Vegfest (UK)|Vegfest]] (14,500 visitors in 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vegfest.co.uk/our-events/|title=Our events|website=VegfestUK|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>) is held in autumn. Plant Powered Expo takes place for the first time in February 2020, just after [[Veganuary]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.plantpoweredexpo.co.uk/|title=Home|website=Plant Powered Expo|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>\n\nLondon Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Kent =====\nMaidstone Vegan Festival took place for the second time on July 29, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maidstoneveganfestival.co.uk/|title=Maidstone Vegan Festival|website=Maidstoneveganfestival.co.uk|language=English|access-date=2017-03-19}}</ref>\n\n===== Newcastle =====\nNewcastle Vegan Festival took place on Sunday 1 July 2018 from 10:30 AM \u2013 4:30 PM UTC+01 in Newcastle upon Tyne.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/newcastleveganfest|title=Newcastle Vegan Festival|website=https://www.facebook.com/newcastleveganfest|language=English|access-date=2018-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/Causes/newcastle-vegan-festival-2018-vegan-awards/1645580835499105/|title=Newcastle VEGAN Festival 2018 + Vegan Awards|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Nottingham =====\nNottingham Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Sheffield =====\nSheffield Vegan Festival will be held on Saturday 15 September 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/sheffieldveganfestival/|title=Sheffield Vegan Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== ''Scotland'' ====\n===== Aberdeen =====\nAberdeen Vegan Festival took place on Sunday 8 July 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/aberdeenveganfest/|title=Aberdeen Vegan Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Cardiff =====\nCardiff Vegan Festival occurred on Saturday 22 September 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/cardiffveganfestival/|title=Log In or Sign Up to View|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Edinburgh =====\nEdinburgh Vegan Festival took place on Sunday 19 August 2018 in Murrayfield Stadium.  This is the first annual Edinburgh Vegan Festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/edinburghveganfest/|title=Edinburgh Vegan Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://veganfestival.co.uk/edinburgh-schools-vegan/|title=Edinburgh Schools Have Gone Plant Based|author=|date=25 April 2018|website=veganfestival.co.uk|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Glasgow =====\nJustVShow is held in July.<ref name=\"auto\"/>  The Glasgow JustVShow is scheduled for July 2\u20133, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.justvshow.co.uk/scotland/|title=Just V Show \u2013 Vegan & Vegetarian Show in Glasgow|website=Glasgow, Scotland, Just V Show}}</ref>  In 2018 the JustVShow is co-locating with The Allergy & Free From Show Scotland 2018.\n\n== North America ==\n\n=== Canada ===\n====Alberta====\n=====Edmonton=====\nThe first Edmonton VegFest was held from 10 am to 6 pm on September 30, 2018, at the Ritchie Community League Hall and Outdoor Park, \n7727 98th Street Northwest, Edmonton, Alberta T6E 5C9. Admission was free. The nonprofit organization coordinating and hosting this annual event was Vegans and Vegetarians of Alberta.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edmontonjournal.com/life/food/new-vegetable-festival-launches-in-ritchie-with-fun-shopping-and-greens|title=New Edmonton vegetable festival in Ritchie offers shopping, greens \u2013 Edmonton Journal|first1=Liane|last1=Faulder|date=20 September 2018|website=edmontonjournal.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.todocanada.ca/vegfest-edmonton/|title=VegFest Edmonton \u2013 Ritchie Community League Hall & Park, 7727 98 Street Northwest, Edmonton|author=|date=|website=To Do Canada|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infoedmonton.com/event/vegfest/|title=VegFest|date=22 August 2019|website=InfoEdmonton|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/vegfest-edmonton-2018/182759825765331/|title=VegFest Edmonton 2018|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/vvoaclub/|title=Vegans and Vegetarians of Alberta|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Ontario====\n=====Guelph=====\nVegfest Guelph<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegfestguelph.ca|title=Vegfest Guelph|website=Vegfest Guelph}}</ref> is an annual festival. The 2016 festival took place on Sunday, September 25, 2016, at Goldie Mill and the Guelph Youth Music Centre.\n\n=====Toronto=====\nThe Vegetarian Food Festival in Toronto attracted over 50,000 attendees in 2014 and featured more than 120 food and product vendors.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegetarian Food Festival Toronto|url=http://veg.ca/festival|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref> It is a free public festival held at Harbourfront Centre by the [[Toronto Vegetarian Association]] in Toronto the second weekend of every September.  It was first held in 1985 and is believed to be the largest and longest continuously running vegetarian food festival in North America, and is credited with having inspired the broad vegetarian food festival movement in the United States, which was first copied by the long-running [[Boston Vegetarian Society|Boston Vegetarian Food Festival]].\n\nThe Toronto Vegan Food and Drink Festival, a fully vegan food and drink festival in the city, strives to present an all vegan experience featuring comfort food, craft brews, wine and spirits.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegan Food and Drink Festival Toronto|url=https://www.vegandrinkfest.com/toronto/}}</ref>\n\nThe Toronto Vegan Expo (formerly known as Vegan Spring Expo) was a free annual vegan festival that took place in Toronto from 2011 to 2013 and had an attendee record of 1500 in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.veganspringexpo.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141222123329/http://www.veganspringexpo.com/|url-status=dead|title=502 Bad Gateway nginx openresty 185.15.56.1|archivedate=22 December 2014|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n=====Niagara (St. Catharines)=====\nNiagara VegFest began in 2012 and is an annual event that takes place in downtown St. Catharines, Ontario.<ref>{{cite web|title=Niagara VegFest|url=http://niagaravegfest.com|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref> The 2012 Niagara VegFest closed with a screening of [[Vegucated]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.getvegucated.com/ |title=Vegucated |publisher=Getvegucated.com |date= |accessdate=2012-09-17}}</ref>\n\n=====Ottawa=====\nThe first Ottawa Veg Fest was held in 2009, and was organized by the National Capital Vegetarian Association.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ottawa Veg Fest|url=http://vegfest.ca|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n=====Kingston=====\nThe first Kingston Veg Fest was held in the fall of 2016. It is being organized by the Kingston Vegetarian Network<ref>{{cite web|title=Kingston Vegetarian Network|url=http://kingstonveg.ca |accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n=====Mississauga=====\nThe first Mississauga Veg Fest was held in May 2018. Mississauga Veg Fest was the city's first vegan festival! Over 60 vendors were in attendance to showcase the GTHA's finest veg-based food, drink, clothing & accessories, products, advocate groups and children's activities. It is being organized by a private volunteer committee<ref>{{cite web|title=Mississauga Veg Fest|url=https://mississaugavegfest.ca |accessdate=21 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n=====Muskoka=====\nMuskoka VegFest had its inaugural event on Aug 11, 2018. 68 Vendors and various speakers drew in a crowd of just under 5000 people.  The annual event is run by a private volunteer committee.  It is a not-for profit event.<ref>{{cite web|title=Muskoka Veg Fest|url=http://muskokavegfest.com|accessdate=8 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Quebec====\n=====Montreal=====\nThe first Montreal Vegan Festival was held from September 26\u201327, 2014 and welcomed over 5,000 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://festivalveganedemontreal.com/2014en/|title=2014\u2013 Montreal Vegan Festival \u2013 September 26\u201327, 2014|website=2014\u2013 Montreal Vegan Festival}}</ref>\n\n====M\u00e9xico====\n\n=====Baja California=====\n\nTijuana Veggie Fest 2018 was held on July 6, 2018, in Centro Cultural Tijuana (CECUT), Paseo de los H\u00e9roes No. 9350, Zona Urbana R\u00edo, Tijuana, Baja California.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/tjveggiefest/tijuana-veggie-fest-2018/148377289195497/|title=Tijuana 