.com/home.html|title=Home|author=|date=|website=Long Beach Vegan Food and Music Festival|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  Co-organizers Edward Yniguez and his wife, Kawani Brown, produce it annually.  Because the first year's event was free, reportedly between 8,500 and 10,000 people showed up throughout the day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lbpost.com/life/food/lbvf-recap/|title=Long Beach Vegan Fest Draws an Estimated 10,000 Attendees to Rainbow Lagoon Park \u2022 Long Beach Post|author=|date=|website=lbpost.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  But 2017 tickets cost $17 (general admission) to $45 (VIP tickets) each.\n\n===== Los Angeles =====\nThe Vegan Street Fair Los Angeles was held on March 25, 2018, at 11223 Chandler Boulevard in North Hollywood, California.\n\nThe Seed Food and Wine LA & Food Festival was held from May 23\u201327, 2018, in [[Los Angeles]], but some scheduling uncertainties remain.\n\nCalifornia Vegetarian Food Festival 2018 is scheduled for September 29, 2018, at Raleigh Studios Hollywood, 5300 Melrose Avenue, [[Los Angeles, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cavegfoodfest.com/|title=Home|author=|date=|website=www.cavegfoodfest.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> U.S. Veg Corp, organizer of this festival, is also organizing the NYC Vegetarian Food Festival 2018, to be held Saturday, May 19, 2018, beginning at 11:00 AM, at Metropolitan Pavilion, [[New York City]], where tickets are $30 \u2013 $75 each.\n\n===== Oakland =====\nOaklandVeg organizes an annual VegWeek in mid-May in [[Oakland, California]].  The 2018 event was held from May 12\u201320, ending with the Oakland VegFest, which was held for May 20, 2018, from 11 am to 5 pm, at the Lake Merritt Amphitheater.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150219143242/http://oaklandveg.com/overview/|title=Overview \u2013 Oakland Veg \u2013 California|author=|date=19 February 2015|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https:/