, at Bainbridge Green, 300 Bainbridge Street, in [[Philadelphia]].  No Philly VegFest had been held in 2016 or 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eventbrite.com/e/46248782353?aff=efbneb|title=Philly VegFest|author=|date=|website=Eventbrite|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.meetup.com/Main-Line-Vegan-Meetup/events/248631069/|title=PHILLY VEG FEST 2018!!!|author=|date=|website=Meetup|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phillymag.com/be-well-philly/2018/04/12/philadelphia-vegan-food-vegfest/|title=Philly's Huge Vegan Food Festival Is Returning in June After a Two-Year Hiatus|author=|date=12 April 2018|website=phillymag.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phillymag.com/be-well-philly/2018/05/24/philadelphia-vegfest-vegan-festival/|title=Take a Look at the Vendors Lined Up for Philly's Huge Vegan Food Festival|author=|date=24 May 2018|website=phillymag.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/PhiladelphiaVegFest/|title=Philadelphia Vegfest|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.paeats.com/|title=PA Eats \u2014 Pennsylvania food + drink videos, recipes and stories|author=|date=|website=PA Eats|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Pittsburgh =====\nThe free annual Pittsburgh VegFest is held every summer in the North Side.<ref>{{cite web|title=PittsburghVegFest|url=http://www.pittsburghvegfest.org/|website=Pittsburghvegfest.org|accessdate=30 June 2016}}</ref>  The inaugural '''Pittsburgh VegFest''' took place in 2015 with an attendance of over 4,000 people from all over the metro area and visitors from Virginia, West Virginia, Erie, Buffalo, Philadelphia and New Jersey.\n\nThe '''Pittsburgh Vegan Festival''' \u2013 Spring Edition \u2013 which was begun in 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/pittsburgh-vegan-festival-spring-edition-2015/1545237529071428/|title=Pittsburgh Vegan Festival \u2013 Spring Edition 2015|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> is scheduled for its fourth year sometime in mid-May at the Unitarian Universal Church of North Hills, 2359 West Ingomar Road, in [[Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania]], and runs from 12 noon to 8 pm.  All children and others under age 16 must be accompanied by an adult in order to be admitted free, and $5 cash admission is charged for all others, at the door.  No pre-event ticket sales is handled.  It is considered to be Pittsburgh's largest vegan event.\n\nThe 11th Pittsburgh Vegan Festival was held on Saturday, October 28, 2017 12\u20136 p.m, and featured Dr. [[Neal Barnard]] of [[Physicians Committee for Responsible Medicine]], among other speakers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/Food/the-11th-pittsburgh-vegan-festival-w-dr-neal-barnard-of-pcrm/1890816304575312/|title=The 11th Pittsburgh Vegan Festival w/ Dr. Neal Barnard of PCRM|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Portland =====\nA vegan beer and food festival is held in Portland in the summer.  The 2019 festival called itself the \"2nd annual.\" <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegoutevents.com/portland2019|title=VegOut! Portland Vegan Beer & Food Festival|website=VegOut!Events Portland 2019}}</ref>\n\nVegFest is a two-day event held in mid-November at the [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]] convention center, with the attendance of many vegan vendors and companies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegfest|url=https://nwveg.org/vegfest|accessdate=13 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== Puerto Rico ====\n===== Fajardo =====\nThe annual bilingual Puerto Rico Vegan Fest was held on February 25, 2018, in the Puerto Rico Convention Center in Fajardo, Puerto Rico.  The annual bilingual Puerto Rico Vegan Fest promotes plant-based diets and vegan values as effective, viable, and sustainable working solutions for human health problems and for ethical and ecological crises.  Attendance is free, as was participation for qualifying tablers promoting plant-based vegan diets and values.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.puertoricoveganfest.com/|title=Pr\u00f3ximo Evento/Next Event|website=Puerto Rico Vegan Fest}}</ref>  The bilingual vegan event was funded by a GoFundMe page.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gofundme.com/puerto-rico-vegan-fest-2018|title=Click here to support Puerto Rico Vegan Fest 2018 organized by Valerie Soto|author=|date=|website=gofundme.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== El Faro (lighthouse) Rincon =====\nThe Puerto Rico Vegan Fest was held in El Faro (lighthouse) Rincon, on Saturday, April 14, 2018.  Attendance and qualifying tabler participation promoting vegan values, food, and practices was free for everyone.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/VegFestPuertoRico/|title=VegFest Puerto Rico|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/380626832364849|title=Puerto Rico VegFest|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Patillas =====\nVive Sano, Vive Mejor Vegan Fest, the Patillas VeganFest, is scheduled for June 4, 2018, from 11 am to 7 pm.  Waleska Rodriguez<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/category/Community/Waleska-Rodr\u00edguez-Lifestyle-375740999109447/|title=Waleska Rodr\u00edguez Lifestyle|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> of mega TV Conectao's por la cocina will be featured, along with many other tablers, speakers, and presenters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/patillasveganfest/|title=Vive Sano, Vive Mejor Vegan Fest|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== South Carolina ====\n===== Mount Pleasant =====\nThe Charleston Sol-Food Veg Fest was held on Saturday, April 28, 2018, from 10 am to 6 pm, at The Grove at [[Patriots Point]] in [[Mount Pleasant, South Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csfvegfest.com/|title=Charleston Sol Veg Fest|last=Kraftives|website=csfvegfest.com}}</ref>  The rain date is May 5, 2018.  It is funded by a GoFundMe page.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gofundme.com/charleston-sol-food-veg-fest|title=Click here to support Charleston Sol Food Veg Fest organized by Charleston Sol Food Veg Fest|website=gofundme.com}}</ref>\n\n==== Tennessee ====\n===== Nashville =====\nThe Third Annual Nashville VegFest was held for April 7, 2018, at the [[Nashville Fairgrounds]] in [[Nashville, Tennessee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nashvillevegfest.com/|title=Nashville VegFest \u2013 Welcome to Nashville VegFest|website=Nashvillevegfest.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>  Tickets are sold, so the event is open to the general public but doesn't offer free admission.\n\n==== Texas ====\n\n===== Austin =====\nThe annual Texas VegFest is held in Austin.<ref>{{cite web|title=Texas VegFest in Austin|url=http://www.texasvegfest.com/|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>  The 2018 Texas VegFest was held April 7, 2018, in Fiesta Gardens at 2101 Jesse E. Segovia Street, [[Austin, Texas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.texasvegfest.com/|title=Texas VegFest|website=Texasvegfest.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref> The 2020 VEGANCHILL Fest \u2013 ATX 2020 is scheduled for February 23, 2020, and the Texas VegFest 2020 is scheduled for Apr 4, 2020, each in [[Austin, Texas|Austin]].\n\n===== Dallas =====\nTexas Veggie Fair is the longest running vegfest in Texas, established 2010 in Dallas. The ninth annual Texas Veggie Fair will be held on Saturday, Oct. 27, 2018, at Reverchon Park in Dallas.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.texasveggiefair.com/|title=Texas Veggie Fair VegFest in Dallas|author=|date=|website=Texas Veggie Fair VegFest in Dallas|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Houston =====\nVegFest Houston is hosted annually by the Vegan Society of P.E.A.C.E. and was first held in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2011|title=VegFest Houston 2011 \u2013 The Premier Vegan Festival of Texas! Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=www.vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  This vegan community festival is dedicated to \"Promoting an ethical, compassionate and sustainable world for all\".<ref>{{cite web|title=VegFest Houston|url=http://www.vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston|website=Vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>  \"VegFest Houston was held at Pecore Hall in 2011 and 2012,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2012|title=VegFest Houston 2012 \u2013 The Premier Vegan Festival of Texas! Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=www.vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and then moved to the larger Pershing Middle School campus for 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2013.php|title=VegFest Houston 2013 \u2013 The Premier Vegan Community Festival of Texas! Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2014|title=VegFest Houston 2014 Vegan Community Festival Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> The festival went on hiatus from 2015\u20132016.  The 6th annual 2018 VegFest Houston was held on July 21, 2018, from 10 am to 5 pm, in Stafford Centre Hall in [[Houston, Texas]], where the 2017 event<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston2017.php|title=VegFest Houston 2017 Society of Peace|author=|date=|website=vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> was staged.<ref>{{cite web|title=VegFest Houston|url=http://www.vegansocietyofpeace.org/vegfesthouston|website=Vegansocietyofpeace.org|accessdate=25 January 2018}}</ref>  The event has been open to the general public and free since its first iteration, but the VIP Pass offers some attractive perks.  The organizers point out that \"Houston is ranked the 4th \"Most Veg-friendly City\" in the nation as of 2012, making us the top Texas Veg-friendly city!\"\n\nThe Vegan Rodeo Weekend \u2013 Houston is scheduled for March 28\u201329, 2020, in Houston.\n\n===== Killeen =====\n[[Killeen, Texas]] is the site of the annual American VegFests<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegevents.com/festivals/|title=Upcoming Plant-Based and Vegan Festivals|author=|date=|website=Veg Events|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> each second Saturday in January.\n\n===== Marshall =====\nHealthFest is an annual free three-day whole foods, plant-based festival that takes place every spring in historic [[Marshall, Texas]], which has been organized annually since 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=HealthFest|url=http://healthfest.com|website=Healthfest.com|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>  The 2017 Health Fest was held from March 31 through April 2, 2017 in the Marshall Civic Center, 2501 East End Blvd, in South Marshall, Texas, with 25 scheduled speakers, and was livestreamed.<ref>{{cite web|title=HealthFest|url=http://healthfest.com/|website=Healthfest.com|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref>  The 2018 3-day event was organized by Fort Worth Vegetarian Society and held at the same site on Saturday, March 31, 2018.\n\n==== Virginia ====\n===== Hampton Roads =====\nHampton Roads VegFest is held every fall in southeastern Virginia, bringing in over 2,000 people from the coastal region.<ref>{{cite web|title=HamptonRoadsVegFest|url=http://www.hamptonroadsvegfest.com/|website=Hamptonroadsvegfest.com|accessdate=8 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n===== Richmond =====\nThe Richmond VegFest is scheduled for June 2018 in Azalea Gardens at Bryan Park in [[Richmond, Virginia]]. About forty vegan food vendors participate, and general admission is free, but attendees buy food from the vendors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://veggiefest.org/|title=Richmond Veg Fest|author=|date=|website=veggiefest.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  Vegan Action and the longstanding Vegetarian Society of Richmond are primary organizers, and major cosponsors include VegFund, FOX Richmond TV, YELP Richmond, several publications, Virginia Family Dentistry with 14-locations practice with 57 general dentists and dental specialists, and a local Indian restaurant.\n\n==== Washington ====\n===== Seattle =====\nThe Seattle VegFest was held on April 7\u20138, 2018, in [[Seattle, Washington]], at the Exhibition Hall at Seattle Center which had been built for the 1962 [[Seattle World's Fair]] just north of [[Belltown, Seattle|Belltown]] in the [[Lower Queen Anne, Seattle|Uptown]] neighborhood.  Admission tickets are sold to the general public, but children under 12 are admitted free.  The sponsor, Vegetarians of Washington, organizes over 1000 volunteers for this annual event.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vegofwa.org/vegfest/|title=Vegfest|date=2 November 2015|website=Vegofwa.org|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Spokane =====\nThe Spokane Vegfest is scheduled for July 28, 2018, from 10am-6pm, at [[Spokane Community College]] in [[Spokane, Washington]].  The annual free event is organized by Inland Northwest Vegans.  Over 3000 attendees participated in the 2017 event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.inveg.org/vegfest/|title=Spokane Vegfest 2019 on July 27 @ Spokane Community College|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Wisconsin ====\n===== Glendale =====\nThe first inaugural Midwest Vegan Fest was held on Saturday, April 14, 2018, at Nicolet High School in [[Glendale, Wisconsin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://midwestveganfest.com/|title=April 14th, 2018 Nicolet High School 11am \u2013 5pm :Midwest Vegan Fest|website=Midwestveganfest.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Madison =====\nMad City Vegan Fest is organized by Alliance for Animals and held in the summer every year in [[Madison, Wisconsin]], and runs from 10 am to 5 pm.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mad City Vegan Fest|url=http://www.veganfest.org/|website=Veganfest.org|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref>  The 2017 event was held June 17, 2017, at the [[Alliant Energy Center]], and the 2018 event is envisioned for June 2018 in the same locale.<ref>https://www.veganfest.org/</ref>\n\n===== Milwaukee =====\nThe Milwaukee Veg Expo was held on Saturday, May 5, 2018, from 11:30 am \u2013 5:30pm, in the Hart Park Muellner Building in [[Milwaukee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mkevegexpo.com/|title=Milwaukee Veg Expo|website=Mkevegexpo.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Oceania ==\n\n=== Australia ===\n{{see also|Vegfest (AU)}}\n\n====Adelaide====\nThe inaugural Vegan Festival Adelaide was in 2007 and the annual event has grown in size ever since, from 1000 attendees in 2007 to 17,000 in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url =https://veganfestival.info/about|website =Vegan festival|title=About|access-date =24 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Sydney ====\n\nThe [[International Vegetarian Union]] encourages regional and national vegetarian organizations to run vegetarian festivals. The [[Vegfest (AU)|43rd World Vegfest]] was held in [[Sydney]] and [[Melbourne]] in October 2015.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|title=43rd World IVU VegFest in Australia|url=http://www.ivu.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=367:ivu-world-vegfest-in-australia&catid=21&Itemid=293|website=IVU.org|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== Melbourne ====\n\nThe [[International Vegetarian Union|IVU]] encourages regional and national organizations to run vegetarian festivals. The 43rd World Vegfest was held in Sydney and Melbourne.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/>\n\nOn November 1, Melbourne celebrates [[World Vegan Day]].<ref>{{cite web|title=World Vegan Day Melbourne|url=http://www.wvd.org.au/|website=Wvd.org.au|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== Hobart ====\n[[Hobart]]'s first vegan festival, VeganFest Tasmania, took place on November 4, 2018. It had been organized as an annual festival celebrating veganism.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://veganfesttas.com.au/ |website=VeganFest Tasmania |accessdate=27 September 2018}}</ref>  The second VeganFest Tasmania is expected to be held on Sunday, 3 November 2019, from 10 am to 4 pm, in the Kingborough Community Hub. Currently at least 48 exhibitors have been scheduled for this free event, which is open to the public.<ref>[http://veganfesttas.com.au/ VeganFest Tasmania]</ref>\n\n== South America ==\n\n===Brazil===\nVegfest Brasil happens since 2004 biennially in a different city each edition. The main organizer is the Brazilian Vegetarian Society (SVB).<br>\nStarting in 2018, Vegfest Brasil will be held annually.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vista-se.com.br/vegfest-aprendizado-polemica-e-tudo-o-que-rolou-no-maior-evento-vegetariano-da-america-latina/|title=Vegfest: aprendizado, pol\u00eamica e tudo o que rolou no maior evento vegetariano da Am\u00e9rica Latina|website=Vista-se.com.br|accessdate=4 September 2017|language=pt}}</ref><br>\n2013: [[Curitiba]]<br>\n2015: [[Recife]]<br>\n2017: [[Campos do Jord\u00e3o]]\n\n===Peru===\n\n==== Arequipa ====\nVegan Fest Arequipa 2018: May 25, 26, 27<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegan Fest Arequipa 2018|url=https://www.facebook.com/veganfestarequipa/|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== Cusco ====\nVegFest Cusco 2017: August 25, 26, 27<ref>{{cite web|title=VegFest Cusco 2017|url=https://www.facebook.com/VegFestPeru/|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[American Vegan Society]]- publishes online list of vegan-oriented VegFests in USA and Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.americanvegan.org/vegfests.htm|title=VegFests in the USA|author=|date=|website=americanvegan.org|accessdate=22 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180717212909/http://www.americanvegan.org/vegfests.htm|archive-date=17 July 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Awareness day]]\n* [[List of food days]]\n* [[List of food months]]\n* [[List of food weeks]]\n* [[List of vegetarian and vegan companies]]\n* [[List of vegetarian organizations]]\n* [[Meat-free days]]\n* [[Vegetarian week]]\n* [[Vegetarianism by country]]\n* [[World Vegan Day]]\n* [[World Vegetarian Day]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Veganism and vegetarianism|state=expanded}}\n\n[[Category:Vegetarianism]]\n[[Category:Veganism]]\n[[Category:Vegetarian festivals|and]]\n[[Category:Lists of food and drink festivals| Vege]]\n", "name_user": "MaynardClark", "label": "safe", "comment": "More DIRECT link to current article on 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_vegetarian_festivals"}
